Thirteen Rules of Excel Style pull these sheets together
one column of left margin, two rows of top margin
left justify single cell inputs, but spill multiple input cells left
right justify single cell outputs, but spill multiple output cells right
default column widths, else 24 for results and 56 for code
one or more source lines per name

test column names in same row as code

no type checking, except for polymorphic dispatch of Python Built-In's
sixteen row height units per source line, rounded down from Format > AutoFit Row Height
don't yield to Excel cutting spaces out of Lambda argument lists
tag overloaded function names with last arg name (eg, "range" and "range_stop" and "range_step")
